Actress Sandra Bullock has given one million dollars to the American Red Cross to boost its tsunami relief campaign, the organisation said Monday. Stars of sound and cinema in Canada are getting in on the fundraising act to help victims of the tsunami, it is reported here Thursday. Among the stars who will take part are : Avril Lavigne, Sarah McLachlan, Sum 41 and the Barenaked Ladies. Canadian record label Nettwerk Management has enlisted some of its big guns to perform in benefit concerts at the end of the month. Canadian Television will broadcast January 29 concert live from Vancouver. 